message.raw:
Bugfix for pulseblaster fixed shot duration workaround.

Sometimes check_status would run in between transition_to_static and start_run,
at which point the instance variables are in an inconsistant state and
an AttributeError is raised. The fix sets all instance variables to None
when they are not in use and check_status now checks only the last attribute
to be set, otherwise concluding that a fixed duration shot is not in progress.

message.raw:
Tested on Python 3 (and 2 after the following changes). Compatibility required:
* Remove unicode_literals as the new MultipartForm threw UnicodeDecodeError
  in Python 2 from urlopen when the request contains the binary file.
* get_content_type needs to return a byte string in both versions. On Python 3,
  the absence of this prevented transition_to_buffered from finishing.
* Fixed bug with calls to http_request instead of self.http_request.
* Checked compileD call on both versions; requires PY2 conditional for a kwarg.

message.raw:
Move boilerplate url request code into separate method, and
have that method use urllib module imports compatible with Python 3.

Convert body of HTTP request to bytes before making HTTP request, and
decode response to unicode before doing regex.

Requires testing.

Without seeing MultipartForm, I don't know if it will be OK with receiving
the unicode strings it is now being given in either Python 2 or 3.

Withthout seeing CompileD, I don't know whether it will be ok with one
of the arguments being a bytestring in Python 3.

message.raw:
Tested on Python 3 (and 2 after the following changes). Compatibility required:
* Absolute import of atsapi and remove duplicate/unnecessary imports.
* sorted() replaces some_dict.keys().sort().
* Replaced the use of np.core.records.fromarrays with a
  structured array using dtype_workaround for brevity.
* Nevertheless, sorting of a structured (or record) array in numpy remains
  impossible across versions without a PY2 conditional.

Fixed a bug with a previously untested warning message.
Added a shutdown method that delays BLACS shutdown if the device is aborting.

This code reliably timesout quickly and throws an exception, halting the worker,
if no trigger pulse arrives. However, if there has been an abort, the abort is successful
but on a subsequent run with a trigger fail something goes wrong with the syncronisation
acquisition_done and a trigger-fail leads to it continuing to write the data to the HDF5 file.

message.raw:
Workaround for problem where spurious PulseBlaster falling edges caused
the novatech to advance its table, despite not being in table mode.

The workaround has it transition to table mode and back again, before going into
table mode for a buffered run. This "double clutch" mechanism appears to reset
its memory pointer to the start of the table. There may still be a potential race
condition in which the PulseBlaster gives its pulses after the double-clutch.
If so, A fix for this might entail imposing an ordering on the devices transitioning
to buffered.
